	for rescuers who are not highly skilled in tracheal intubation. Bystander
	cardiopulmonary resuscitation increases survival rates from out-of-hospital
	cardiac arrest. Following a witnessed, sudden collapse, survival
	rates achieved when bystanders deliver compression-only cardiopulmonary
	resuscitation are at least the same as those achieved with cardiopulmonary
	resuscitation that includes mouth-to-mouth ventilation (rescue breathing).
